   493                        USER_TIMEOUT
   494                        ; Once the partition block is loaded and signature verified, a timeout os started to
   495                        ; allow the user to jump into the Monitor code instead of default booting from the
   496                        ; IDE drive. This is also a safety in case the Boot Record is either damaged or
   497                        ; incorrectly configured as well as the boot image loaded by the Boot Record has any
   498                        ; issues. A default 5 seconds timeout should be sufficient to allow the user to interrupt
   499                        ; the boot process. The "ESC" key will be used to interrupt the boot and enter the Monitor.
   500                        ;
