  1786                        ;Configuration Data - The following tables contains the default data used for:
  1787                        ; - Reset of the SC28L92 (RESET_28L92 routine)
  1788                        ; - Init of the SC28L92 (INIT_28L92 routine)
  1789                        ; - Basic details for register definitions are below, consult SC28L92 DataSheet
  1790                        ; - Note: Output Port bits OP0/OP1 must be set for RTS to work on Ports A and B
  1791                        ;
  1792                        ;Mode Register 0 definition
  1793                        ; Bit7          ;Rx Watchdog Control
  1794                        ; Bit6          ;RX-Int(2) Select
  1795                        ; Bit5/4        ;Tx-Int fill level
  1796                        ; Bit3          ;FIFO size
  1797                        ; Bit2          ;Baud Rate Extended II
  1798                        ; Bit1          ;Test 2 (don't use)
  1799                        ; Bit0          ;Baud Rate Extended I
  1800                        ;
  1801                        ;Mode Register 1 definition
  1802                        ; Bit7          ;RxRTS Control - 1 = Yes
  1803                        ; Bit6          ;RX-Int(1) Select
  1804                        ; Bit5          ;Error Mode - 0 = Character
  1805                        ; Bit4/3        ;Parity Mode - 10 = No Parity
  1806                        ; Bit2          ;Parity Type - 0 = Even (doesn't matter)
  1807                        ; Bit1/0        ;Bits Per Character - 11 = 8
  1808                        ;
  1809                        ;Mode Register 2 Definition
  1810                        ; Bit7/6        ;Channel Mode   - 00 = Normal
  1811                        ; Bit5          ;TxRTS Control - 0 = Yes
  1812                        ; Bit4          ;TxCTS Enable - 1 = Yes
  1813                        ; Bit3-0        ;Stop Bits - 0111 = 1 Stop Bit
  1814                        ;
  1815                        ;Baud Rate Clock Definition (Extended Mode I)
  1816                        ; Upper 4 bits = Receive Baud Rate
  1817                        ; Lower 4 bits = Transmit Baud Rate
  1818                        ; for 115.2K setting is %11001100
  1819                        ; Also set ACR Bit7 = 1 for extended rates (115.2K)
  1820                        ;
  1821                        ;Command Register Definition
  1822                        ; Bit7-4        ;Special commands
  1823                        ; Bit3          ;Disable Transmit
  1824                        ; Bit2          ;Enable Transmit
  1825                        ; Bit1          ;Disable Receive
  1826                        ; Bit0          ;Enable Receive
  1827                        ;
  1828                        ;Aux Control Register Definition
  1829                        ; Bit7          ;BRG Set Select - 1 = Extended
  1830                        ; Bit6-5-4      ;Counter/Timer operating mode 110 = Counter mode from XTAL
  1831                        ; Bit3-2-1-0    ;Enable IP3-2-1-0 Change Of State (COS) IRQ
  1832                        ;
  1833                        ;Interrupt Mask Register Definition
  1834                        ; Bit7          ;Input Change Interrupt 1 = On
  1835                        ; Bit6          ;Change Break B Interrupt 1 = On
  1836                        ; Bit5          ;RxRDY B Interrupt 1 = On
  Sat Apr  4 2026 16:30                                                                                                    Page 37


  1837                        ; Bit4          ;TxRDY B Interrupt 1 = On
  1838                        ; Bit3          ;Counter Ready Interrupt 1 = On
  1839                        ; Bit2          ;Change Break A Interrupt 1 = On
  1840                        ; Bit1          ;RxRDY A Interrupt 1 = On
  1841                        ; Bit0          ;TxRDY A Interrupt 1 = On
