  1843                        CFG_TABLE       ;Configuration table for hardware devices
  1844                        ;
  1845                        ;Data commands are sent in reverse order from list. This list is the default initialization for
  1846                        ; the DUART as configured for use as a Console connected to either ExtraPutty(WIN) or Serial(OSX)
  1847                        ; The data here is copied to page $02 and is used to configure the DUART during boot up. The soft
  1848                        ; data can be changed and the core INIT_28L92 routine can be called to reconfigure the DUART.
  1849                        ; NOTE: the register offset data is not kept in soft config memory as the initialization
  1850                        ; sequence should not be changed!
  1851                        ;
  1852                        ; Both serial ports are configured at startup!
  1853                        ; - Port A is used as the console.
  1854                        ; - Port B is in idle mode or used for Reader/Punch (DOS/65).
  1855                        ;
  1856                        INIT_DUART       ;Start of DUART Initialization Data
  1857 00:FE60: 03                           .DB     %00000011       ;Enable OP0/1 for RTS control Port A/B
  1858 00:FE61: 0A                           .DB     %00001010       ;Disable Receiver/Disable Transmitter B
  1859 00:FE62: 09                           .DB     %00001001       ;Enable Receiver/Disable Transmitter A
  1860 00:FE63: 0F                           .DB     %00001111       ;Interrupt Mask Register setup
  1861 00:FE64: E0                           .DB     %11100000       ;Aux Register setup for Counter/Timer
  1862 00:FE65: 48                           .DB     %01001000       ;Counter/Timer Upper Preset
  1863 00:FE66: 00                           .DB     %00000000       ;Counter/Timer Lower Preset
  1864 00:FE67: CC                           .DB     %11001100       ;Baud Rate clock for Rcv/Xmt - 115.2K B
  1865 00:FE68: CC                           .DB     %11001100       ;Baud Rate clock for Rcv/Xmt - 115.2K A
  1866 00:FE69: 30                           .DB     %00110000       ;Reset Transmitter B
  1867 00:FE6A: 20                           .DB     %00100000       ;Reset Receiver B
  1868 00:FE6B: 30                           .DB     %00110000       ;Reset Transmitter A
  1869 00:FE6C: 20                           .DB     %00100000       ;Reset Receiver A
  1870 00:FE6D: 00                           .DB     %00000000       ;Interrupt Mask Register setup
  1871 00:FE6E: F0                           .DB     %11110000       ;Command Register A - disable Power Down
  1872                        INIT_DUART_E    ;End of DUART Initialization Data
  1873                        ;
  1874 00:FE6F: FF                           .DB     $FF             ;Spare byte for offset to MR data
  1875                        ;
  1876                        ;Mode Register Data is defined separately. Using the loop routine above to send this data to
  1877                        ; the DUART does not work properly. See the description of the problem using Indexed addressing
  1878                        ; to load the DUART registers above. This data is also kept in soft config memory in page $02.
