  2028                        ;
  2029                        ;This front end for the IRQ vector, saves the CPU registers and determines if a BRK instruction
  2030                        ; was the cause. There are 25 clock cycles to jump to the IRQ vector, and there are 26 clock cycles
  2031                        ; to jump to the BRK vector. Note that there is an additional 18 clock cycles for the IRQ return
  2032                        ; vector, which restores the registers. This creates an overhead of 43 (IRQ) or 44 (BRK) clock
  2033                        ; cycles, plus whatever the ISR or BRK service routines add.
  2034                        ;
  2035                        IRQ_VECTOR                              ;This is the ROM start for the BRK/IRQ handler
  2036 00:FF84: 48                           PHA                     ;Save A Reg (3)
  2037 00:FF85: DA                           PHX                     ;Save X Reg (3)
  2038 00:FF86: 5A                           PHY                     ;Save Y Reg (3)
  2039 00:FF87: BA                           TSX                     ;Get Stack pointer (2)
  2040 00:FF88: BD 04 01                     LDA     $0100+4,X       ;Get Status Register (4)
  2041 00:FF8B: 29 10                        AND     #$10            ;Mask for BRK bit set (2)
